{% doc %}

  Product Meta Card
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Horizontal card primitive used on the PDP info column:
    - 48×48 image on the left (muted-square fallback if no image passed)
    - details stack on the right (12px leading-16 text)
    - `bg-bg-surface` (warm beige) rounded-6 container

  Two concrete consumers today — extracted here so their markup can't drift
  independently:
    - `product-match-with.liquid` — per-pairing card, clickable (href =
      related product URL), body = title + color dots + price.
    - `product-model-info.liquid` — fit-reference card, NOT clickable, body
      = model name + height + size lines.

  If `href` is set, the root element renders as `<a>`; otherwise as `<div>`.
  Everything inside the details stack is caller-owned: pass a `body`
  capture from the calling snippet.

  @param {string} alt     - Alt text for the image + aria-label on the root when the card is a link. Required.
  @param {string} body    - Captured HTML for the details stack (title line, meta lines, etc). Required.
  @param {object} [image] - Image or media_image object. Falls back to a muted square placeholder.
  @param {string} [href]  - Link URL. If set, root is <a>; otherwise <div>.

  @example
    {% capture body %}
      <p class="text-[12px] font-medium uppercase truncate w-full">{{ related.title }}</p>
      <p class="text-[12px]">{{ related.price | money_without_trailing_zeros }}</p>
    {% endcapture %}
    {% render 'product-meta-card',
              href: related.url,
              image: related.featured_image,
              alt: related.title,
              body: body %}

{% enddoc %}

{%- comment -%}
  `leading-[16px]` on the details stack — matches across both consumers so
  baselines align when a Match With card and a Model Info card render side
  by side in the PDP info-column row (see `product-detail-form.liquid`).
  `min-w-0 flex-1` is load-bearing: without it, long text pushes the card
  past its parent's width and `truncate` / `line-clamp` never kick in.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% if href != blank %}
  <a
    href="{{ href }}"
    class="flex items-center gap-3 pl-3 pr-4 py-3 rounded-[6px] bg-bg-surface"
    {% if alt != blank %}aria-label="{{ alt | escape }}"{% endif %}
  >
{% else %}
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 pl-3 pr-4 py-3 rounded-[6px] bg-bg-surface">
{% endif %}

  {% if image %}
    {{ image
      | image_url: width: 96
      | image_tag:
        loading: 'lazy',
        class: 'w-12 h-12 rounded-[4px] object-cover shrink-0',
        alt: alt,
        sizes: '48px'
    }}
  {% else %}
    <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-[4px] bg-muted shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-[2px] items-start leading-[16px] text-fg min-w-0 flex-1">
    {{ body }}
  </div>

{% if href != blank %}
  </a>
{% else %}
  </div>
{% endif %}
